CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 8, 1947, pg. 17, reads: "Kiddies' Celebrate - Little Paula Banks, granddaughter of Mr. and Mrs. George Banks of Bentley Drive, celebrated her fifth birthday recently. Some of the neighborhood kiddies are shown during the gay party which was quite an affair for a charming young lass. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Paula Banks holding cake for her fifth birthday party, surrounded by children holding party favors and gathered on floral chair and sofa, in home of George W. Banks
